args: This here is called a ＂tansu,＂ and yer\ndarn tootin' it's got shady omikuji!
Omikuji are fortunes, right? Those little\nslips of paper with the writing on 'em?
Right. Back in Hinomoto, we draw 'em to\nlearn if our luck's gonna be good or bad.
Yessir, but THESE omikuji ain't\nyer average fortunes.
Be it good or bad, the stuff written on\nthese puppies ALWAYS comes true.
Well that's soundin' less like a fortune\nand more like a prophecy.
Yes, that seems far beyond the realm \nof mere fortunetelling.
Which is why Lord Seimei always\ncomes 'round to exorcise 'em.
And THAT'S why yers truly is guardin'\nthis tansu until he can show up and\ngive it the business.
Hello, everyone. What's going on here?
Oh, we were just discussing omikuji.
I am...not familiar with the term.
Wheeeee hee hee hee ha ha hoooo!
(The flying Pipple sent me stumbling,\nand then...)
(I feel as though I knocked something\nover during my fall.)
I'm well, thank you. Just a little spill.
Might someone please inform me\nwhat exactly these ＂omikuji＂ are?
These ain't just any omikuji—they're\nSHADY omikuji! And when the tansu got\nknocked over, it sent one of 'em a'flyin'!
Here, go on n' take it!
It reads ＂Fortune: Bunlucky＂?\nWhatever does THAT mean?
Beats me. Omikuji normally come\nin yer usual lucky and unlucky flavors,\nbut that there's a new one.
＂Bunlucky＂ is like bread, yeah?\nOr maybe it's talking about bunnies?\n...Wait, is it even a WORD?
＂Bunlucky: All's well that ends well.\n'Hop' you have sweet dreams.＂
＂Your wish will be foiled by another's\ninterference. Too bad, so sad!＂
＂The one you await isn't coming,\nso go seek them out yourself.＂
＂What's lost is often found right under\nyour nose, but keep your eyes up.＂
＂In travels, beware fire and water.\nIn business, you're in the way. Just don't.＂
＂In love, you're unstoppable—and the one\nyou fancy will sit up and take notice.\nGo get 'im, snuggle bunny!＂
Guess that ain't as bad as it COULD be?
Still, if all that is written comes to pass,\nit sounds like quite the gauntlet.
Shady or not, this is a mere fortune.\nThere's no need to worry ourselves\nsilly over it.
Nothing will come of—Hm? There is\nsomething beneath that statue...
That's...my novel! Oh, I have been\nsearching for this for so very long!
It is a favorite of mine, and I was terribly\nsad when I realized it had gone missing.
To think I passed it by a hundredfold times\nor more and never noticed! It truly was\nright under my...
The statue's falling! OUTTA THE WAY!
Goodness, but that was close!\nIt's a lucky thing no one was hurt.
I find all of this to be exceedingly strange.\nWhy would a statue suddenly topple over\nof its own accord?
It's just as the omikuji predicted...
She's right! Remember what it said?\n＂What's lost is often found right under yer\nnose, but keep yer dang eyes up!＂
Does that mean everything ELSE in that\nfortune is gonna come true next?!

Ain't nothin' to do for it but stay
on yer toes and keep a sharp eye.
'Cause if ya don't, ya can kiss yer
pretty little life goodbye!
(The year has only begun, and I already\nfind myself off to an inauspicious start...)
